# Project context and memory (Cursor)

## What to persist

Use durable project knowledge when it should survive a single chat:

- **Architecture**: Realms, databases, module layout, integration points
- **Critical issues**: Race conditions, null-check hazards, production safety
- **Patterns**: How this fork deploys, tests, and rolls back
- **User preferences**: Explicit “always do X” requests

## Where it lives in Cursor

- **Cursor Memories** (user-level): Stable facts the user asks you to remember across projects/sessions
- **This repository**: `.cursor/rules/` (standards), `.cursor/reference/` (archives and summaries), module `README.md` files, and SQL/C++ comments for implementation detail
- **Notion (Old Man Warcraft)**: Server topology, runbooks, and operational detail—**use the Notion MCP** (`notion-search`, `notion-fetch`) instead of guessing ports, hostnames, or procedures
- **AzerothCore MCP** (`user-azerothcore`): Live DB/SOAP/wiki helpers for SmartAI, spells, conditions, quests—use for data-backed debugging when the server is reachable (see `.cursor/rules/mcp-usage.mdc`)
- **Other MCP servers** (GitLab, GitHub, OMW API, fetch, deepwiki, exa, firecrawl, sequential-thinking, browser): Use per `.cursor/rules/mcp-usage.mdc` and **`.cursor/reference/mcp-tools-inventory.md`**; never substitute them for secrets stored outside the repo

## Before high-risk work

Search or recall context for:

- Playerbot group, arena, and guild code paths
- Production database or shared `acore_world` changes
- SmartAI phase chains and spell proc interactions

If nothing is documented yet, add a short note in the repo (for example under `.cursor/reference/` or the relevant module docs) instead of relying only on chat history.

## Knowledge shape (if using a graph-style store)

When storing structured knowledge elsewhere, prefer:

- **Clear names**: e.g. `mod-playerbots-llm Module`, not vague `LLM module`
- **Atomic facts**: One observation per fact; no speculation
- **Relations**: `depends_on`, `integrates_with`, `uses`, etc., when they add clarity
- **Safety first**: Document race conditions and production constraints immediately

## Maintenance

- Refresh or remove stale notes after major refactors or module additions
- Keep “critical safety” items aligned with code and `.cursor/rules/playerbots-rules.mdc`

## Integration with migrated Windsurf material

Static guidance lives in `.cursor/rules/` (formerly `.windsurf/rules/`). Long-form archive: `.cursor/reference/windsurf-rules-archive.md`. Workflows and references are under `.cursor/skills/` and `.cursor/docs/`. The `.augment/` tree was removed intentionally; use `.cursor/` as canonical.
